	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />If describing an event that happens less than one minute into a game is an inexcusable <a href="https://allthetropes.org/wiki/First_Episode_Spoiler" class="postlink">first-episode spoiler</a>, think about it from the perspective of someone who has played Action 52, tries a familiarly named game in Action 53, and concludes that Action 53 has even worse quality control than Action 52. And even if players do get past it, you run the risk of <a href="https://allthetropes.org/wiki/All_There_Is_to_Know_About_%22The_Crying_Game%22" class="postlink">players remembering the game only for the twist</a>.<br /><br />What other games' marketing has successfully pulled off hiding everything past the <a href="https://allthetropes.org/wiki/Fake-Out_Opening" class="postlink">fake-out opening</a>?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
